roast /rəʊst/

(roasting,roasted,roasts) 

1. V-T When you roast meat or other food, you cook it by dry heat in an oven or over a fire. 烤 

例： I personally would rather roast a chicken whole. 我个人更愿意烤整鸡。 

2. ADJ Roast meat has been cooked by roasting. 烤熟了的 [ADJ n] 

例： They serve the most delicious roast beef. 他们做最美味的烤牛肉。 

3. N-COUNT A roast is a piece of meat that is cooked by roasting. 烤肉 

例： Come into the kitchen. I've got to put the roast in. 到厨房里来。我得把烤肉放进去。

